        <body>
            <head>249. Memorandum From the Special Assistant to the Deputy Secretary of State
                    (<persName corresp="recoqpx2aNuHTDUHK">Timbie</persName>) to Secretary of State
                    <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName>
                <note n="1" place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d249fn1">Source: Department of State,
                    Bureau of Arms Control and Disarmament, Lot 01D127, 1969–1990 Subject Records of
                        <persName corresp="recoqpx2aNuHTDUHK">James P. Timbie</persName>, Box 1,
                        <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_INF_1"
                        >INF</gloss> 1987. Secret.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1987-12-09"
                        >December 9, 1987</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>We have made some progress today on <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss>. A sheet summarizing the differences is attached. The steps forward
                are:</p>
            <quote>
                <p>—<persName corresp="recIjriLJ5q37CiAe">Akhromeyev</persName> has agreed to put
                    the 50% <rs type="topic" corresp="reclksm3VX3UUxetF">throw weight</rs> cut in
                    the <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recHvtjt4uCqCi2Qk">Treaty</rs>.</p>
                <p>—1540 <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs> on 154 heavy
                    missiles is agreed.</p>
                <p>—<persName corresp="recIjriLJ5q37CiAe">Akhromeyev</persName> agrees on a ceiling
                    on <rs type="topic" corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">ballistic missile</rs>
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs>, and proposes to
                    negotiate on a number between 4800 and 5100. He suggests dropping all other <rs
                        corresp="recNg1LuXkmZCFR19" type="topic">sublimits</rs>.</p>
                <p>—He agrees to attribute numbers of <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga"
                        >warheads</rs> to <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                        <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                    </gloss> and <gloss target="#t_SLBM_1">
                        <rs corresp="recnGcR0g6J7yKHTE" type="topic">SLBMs</rs>
                    </gloss>, and we agree on the numbers for both sides’ existing <gloss
                        target="#t_ICBM_1">
                        <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBMs</rs>
                    </gloss> and on numbers for U.S. <gloss target="#t_SLBM_1">
                        <rs corresp="recnGcR0g6J7yKHTE" type="topic">SLBMs</rs>
                    </gloss>. (He hasn’t given us Soviet <rs corresp="recnGcR0g6J7yKHTE"
                        type="topic">SLBM</rs> numbers yet). He wants to base the numbers of <rs
                        type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs>, however, on the
                    maximum tested; whereas we want to verify the number by <rs type="topic"
                        corresp="reclbsHvbXLer8sMP">on-site inspection</rs> of deployed
                    missiles.</p>
                <p>—Soviets agree to ban <rs type="topic" corresp="recXyi0y36LV93Itc">encryption of
                        telemetry</rs>.</p>
            </quote>
            <pb facs="1145" n="1118" xml:id="pg_1118"/>
            <p>We are far apart on <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCMs</rs>
                </gloss> and on rules attributing numbers of <gloss target="#t_ALCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic">ALCMs</rs>
                </gloss> to <rs type="topic" corresp="rectLhSs11Y4ZQ6zE">bombers</rs>. (He says
                there will be no <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>
                <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recHvtjt4uCqCi2Qk">Treaty</rs> and no joint
                statement unless we work something out on <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCMs</rs>
                </gloss>.) The Soviet paper<note n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d249fn2">Reference is to
                        <ref target="#d247fn2">footnote 2, Document 247</ref>.</note> this morning
                would constrain only nuclear-armed <gloss target="#t_ALCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic">ALCMs</rs>
                </gloss>, but this appears to have been a mistake, and the Soviets have bracketed
                the term “nuclear-armed,” so there is no progress to report on this issue.</p>
            <p>The drafting group has produced general <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                    <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                </gloss> language to capture the above situation and refer everything else to
                Geneva. The text that has been agreed is good. We are negotiating language on <gloss
                    target="#t_SLCM_1">
                    <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCMs</rs>
                </gloss>.</p>
            <p>On <rs type="event" corresp="rec0rc9kDG6TIF88N">defense and space</rs>, <persName
                    corresp="recIjriLJ5q37CiAe">Akhromeyev</persName> emphasizes the October joint
                statement, which he says is the basis of <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl"
                    >Gorbachev</persName>’s visit, and which he says we are walking back. Working
                out some language in this area is the other major objective for tonight.</p>
            <frus:attachment xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
                <note>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Attachment</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="simple_bold">Paper Prepared in the Department of State</hi>
                    <note n="3" place="foot" xml:id="d249fn3">No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1987-12-09">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss>
                </p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">1.</hi>
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="reclksm3VX3UUxetF">Throw Weight</rs>
                </p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Record commitment in <rs
                                    type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recHvtjt4uCqCi2Qk"
                                    >Treaty</rs>
                            </hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: Could be common
                                document</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">2.</hi>
                    <rs corresp="recNg1LuXkmZCFR19" type="topic">Sublimits</rs>
                </p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recr08QgEMEm1Bk04">Ballistic Missile</rs>
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">Warheads</rs>
                </p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: 4800</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: 5100</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                        <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBM</rs>
                    </gloss> and <rs corresp="recnGcR0g6J7yKHTE" type="topic">SLBM</rs>
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">Warheads</rs>
                </p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: 3300 <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                                    <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBM</rs>
                                </gloss>
                                <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs>, no <rs
                                    type="topic" corresp="recNg1LuXkmZCFR19">sublimit</rs> on <rs
                                    corresp="recnGcR0g6J7yKHTE" type="topic">SLBM</rs>
                                <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs>
                            </hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: 3300 <gloss
                                    target="#t_ICBM_1">
                                    <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBM</rs>
                                </gloss>
                                <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs> and 3300
                                    <rs corresp="recnGcR0g6J7yKHTE" type="topic">SLBM</rs>
                                <rs type="topic" corresp="recfkRWjb8Vcm4Gga">warheads</rs>, or drop
                                both. Assert they will not deploy more than 3300 <gloss
                                    target="#t_ICBM_1">
                                    <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBM</rs>
                                </gloss>
                                <gloss target="#t_RV_1">RVs</gloss>.</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <pb facs="1146" n="1119" xml:id="pg_1119"/>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">3.</hi>
                    <rs type="topic" corresp="recTaee7UxoGjTDrc">Counting Rules</rs>
                </p>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <gloss target="#t_ALCM_1">
                        <rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic">ALCMs</rs>
                    </gloss>
                </p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Attribute 6 per bomber equipped for <gloss
                                    target="#t_ALCM_1">
                                    <rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic">ALCMS</rs>
                                </gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: Attribute a number
                                reflecting the maximum capability for each bomber type, inspection
                                (can’t resolve here)</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <gloss target="#t_ALCM_1">
                        <rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic">ALCMs</rs>
                    </gloss> Covered by <gloss target="#t_START_1">
                        <rs type="event" corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O">START</rs>
                    </gloss>
                </p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Nuclear-armed; range over 1500 km</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: Bracketed “nuclear-armed”
                                (answer in the morning) range over 600 km</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">Soviet <rs corresp="recnGcR0g6J7yKHTE" type="topic"
                        >SLBM</rs> and some <gloss target="#t_ICBM_1">
                        <rs corresp="reccap2GMokKh4v4P" type="topic">ICBM</rs>
                    </gloss> Warhead Numbers</p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Soviets should provide numbers</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: Numbers in the morning</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p rendition="#sectiontitleital">
                    <hi rendition="#roman">4.</hi>
                    <gloss target="#t_SLCM_1">
                        <rs corresp="recRMohN3AY0ch5I7" type="topic">SLCMs</rs>
                    </gloss>
                </p>
                <table cols="2">
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">US: Find mutually acceptable solution; seek
                                effective <rs corresp="recvMEtDFpnXkyj45" type="topic"
                                    >verification</rs>
                            </hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#roman">
                                <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>: Limits on numbers and
                                platforms</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </frus:attachment>
        </body>
    </text>
